OL,3,CRenewed water safety appeal to public
OL,4,Cas accidental drownings spiked in 2023
OL,6,FAs summer starts to break in the UK,
OL,7,Fand warmer weather is expected to come
OL,8,Fwith it, a renewed water safety plea
OL,9,Fis being made to the public.
OL,11,FAnnual figures released by the
OL,12,FNational Water Safety Forum (NWSF)
OL,13,Fhave revealed that in 2023 accidental
OL,14,Fdrownings rose to 236 - 10 more than
OL,15,F2022.
OL,17,FAnd, as we enter June, which saw more
OL,18,Fwater-related deaths in the UK than
OL,19,Fany other month last year, the NWSF
OL,20,Fhas kick-started their campaign.
