OL,3,CRenewed water safety appeal to public
OL,4,Cas accidental drownings spiked in 2023
OL,6,FExperts have warned that warmer
OL,7,Fweather may not correlate to warmer
OL,8,Fwaters, and that swimmers are still at
OL,9,Frisk of cold water shock and
OL,10,Faccidental drowning.
OL,12,FThe 2023 Water Incident Database
OL,13,F(WAID) figures also show that once
OL,14,Fagain most accidental deaths in water
OL,15,Foccurred inland - 63% were in rivers,
OL,16,Fcanals, lakes, reservoirs and quarries
OL,17,F` and males are still the
OL,18,Foverwhelmingly majority of victims -
OL,19,F83%.
